European Coal Rises in London Trading, Has Fourth Straight Gain

-- B y   A l i s t a i r   H o l l o w a y
-- 
2011-06-01T08:15:21Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-01/european-coal-rises-in-london-trading-has-fourth-straight-gain.html
European coal derivatives rose in
early  London  trading, for a fourth straight advance.  Coal for delivery to Amsterdam, Rotterdam or Antwerp with
settlement next year rose 60 cents, or 0.5 percent, to $130 a
metric ton by 9:10 a.m. in London.  The data are drawn from information supplied by ICAP Plc,
 GFI Group Inc. (GFIG) , Spectron Group Ltd., Credit Suisse Group AG, IHS
McCloskey, Bloomberg, Tradition Financial Services and Tullett
Prebon Plc.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alistair Holloway in London at 
 aholloway1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Carpenter at 
 ccarpenter2@bloomberg.net  